This paper deals with voice conversion, which is a subfield of speech processing. The paper specifically focuses on the use of Mel-spectrogram augmentation to improve the performance of a sequence-to-sequence voice conversion model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper also involves natural language processing techniques. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
